Privacy Policy
FlickDirect Privacy Policy
1. Personal Information We Collect
FlickDirect collects personal data to provide services and enhance user experience. The information collected depends on your interactions with our website and mobile app.
We do not sell, rent, trade, or share your personal information with any third parties, service providers, advertisers, or external entities.
All data collected remains strictly within FlickDirect for the sole purpose of delivering our services.
User Data
– Name, email, contact details, and preferences.
Technical Data
– IP address, browser type, and device type.
Transactional Data
– Purchases and subscriptions.
Usage Data
– Pages visited, content interactions, and engagement metrics.
Mobile App Data
– Username, password, and movies interests.
2. Mobile App Subscriptions & Cancellation
FlickDirect does not manage billing, subscriptions, or refunds for the mobile app. If you have an active subscription, you must cancel it directly through the platform where you purchased it:
Apple App Store:
Manage or cancel subscriptions via
Apple's subscription settings
.
Google Play Store:
Manage or cancel subscriptions via
Google Play's subscription settings
.
Note:
Deleting the app does not automatically cancel subscriptions. Refund requests must be handled directly through Apple or Google, subject to their policies.
3. Governing Law & Jurisdiction
This Privacy Policy shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the State of
Florida
, without regard to its conflict of law provisions.
Any
legal disputes or claims
shall be exclusively resolved in
Palm Beach County, Florida
. Users agree that any claims arising out of or related to this Privacy Policy or the use of FlickDirect's services shall be filed
only in state or federal courts within Palm Beach County, Florida
.
4. Binding Arbitration & Mediation Agreement
Any disputes or claims arising from this Privacy Policy, the use of FlickDirect's website, or its mobile app must be resolved
through binding arbitration in Palm Beach County, Florida
, rather than court litigation, except that claims may be brought in
small claims court if they qualify
.
Arbitration Rules:
Arbitration will be conducted by the
American Arbitration Association (AAA)
under its rules.
Both parties must first
attempt mediation
before proceeding with arbitration.
Each party is responsible for its own legal fees, except where prohibited by law.
No Class Action Lawsuits:
Users
waive the right
to participate in class-action lawsuits. All claims must be
filed individually
and cannot be combined with others.
5. Google & YouTube API Services
We integrate Google services, including YouTube API. By using our services, you agree to be bound by the
YouTube Terms of Service
and
Google Privacy Policy
.
